<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Tangletrees</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Celia Tinker – Written evidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Draft Deregulation </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Bill :</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Suggested Addition Reduces Bureaucracy and is </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Beneficial .</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> ‘Use of Land’ </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Suggest all Byways Open to All Traffic (BOATs) in National Parks </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">are</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> classified as Restricted Byways.   </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">My suggestion relates to saving time and funds of local authority officers. It simplifies the law and safeguards special areas of countryside from noise and pollution for safe and quiet enjoyment by the public. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">It is to stop off-</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">roading</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">, with mechanically propelled vehicles, in all National Parks.   Probably the simplest way of stopping 4x4s and trail bikes etc. would be for all unsealed Byways Open to All Traffic (BOATs) in National Parks to be re-designated as Restricted Byways. This would be in line with the statutory origin of Restricted Byways under the Countryside and Rights of Way Act and the Natural Environment and Rural Communities Act. Furthermore the latter Act allows National Park Authorities to apply Traffic Regulation Orders (TROs) recognising the special nature of National Parks.  Having no off-</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">roading</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> with mechanically propelled vehicles would further the purposes of National Parks which are:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#555555; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">1. Conserve and enhance the natural beauty, wildlife and cultural heritage</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">2. Promote opportunities for the understanding and enjoyment of the special qualities of National Parks by the Public.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Savings: not having to maintain rights of way damaged by motorised vehicles.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Saving officers time in considering increasing requests for Traffic Regulation Orders in National Parks. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Avoiding accidents by providing rights of way that are safe for </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">horseriders</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">, pedal cyclists and walkers.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">I have some knowledge from living near the South Downs. When many paths were classified as RUPPS, there was increasing heavy use by motorised vehicles – trail bikes and 4x4s, resulting in damage to paths. Some </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">horseriders</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> feared to go there </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">any more</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">. It was a wonderful improvement and relief when restricted byways were introduce by statute. As there </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">are</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> no Byways Open to All Traffic in our area, we are able to conserve the natural beauty in this National Park. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">30 August 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>